&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="hidden quarto-markdown-envelope-contents" data-render-id="cXVhcnRvLXR3aXR0ZXJjYXJkZGVzYw=="&gt;Grab Issues in Parallel: grab several provably-independent open issues and work them concurrently — one worktree-isolated subagent per issue, each implementing its issue, opening an MR/PR, and ARDI-ing it to clean. The parallel counterpart to the deliberately-serial &lt;code&gt;gii&lt;/code&gt;. Use when asked to ‘gip’, ‘grab issues in parallel’, ‘work several issues at once’, ‘parallelize the backlog’, ‘do these issues concurrently’, or ‘fan out the issue queue’.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
